replyContent: Hi Darren, thank you for your feedback. As we are using Google's API for multiplayer each player needs her own account. Note though that a device can have several Google accounts active so you could create an account for each player, add it to the device in the device settings. Then when signing in within the game you get the option to choose.

I opened up the free Dragon Fly! game and was presented with an offer for Dragon Fly paid for 1/3 of the original price.  When I went to the market, it was regular price ~ $2.   Later that day the offer is for 50% off.  The developer(s) need to be more careful about planning and executing their promotions.   I almost didn't buy it for a $1, but I wanted to be able to point this out.  The free version was fun, but when they went to this paid model they really make it feel like they are trying to squeeze you into buying the paid version.   I don't mind providing incentive, however I feel like they took it too far.  More power to them for finding ways to add to the game, but they should be more balanced in their attempts to convert free users to paid users.  Look at Angry Birds series for example:   They started off at $1 with an option of the free ad supported FULL version of the game that wasn't gimped.  Sometimes they give away the no-ad versions away for free on Android Market and Amazon Android App Market.   They have been pretty successful and they continually update the games adding new levels / challenges.    I'm just saying that it can be done in a much nicer way.
